\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104daw1665702678607.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/daw1665702678607.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/daw1665702678607.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"daw1665702678607\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">[USER_3GL]\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"daw1665702678607___usergl__468523\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the [USER_3GL] section of the assignment file to lists third-party components and Uniface 3GL extensions to be made available to Uniface.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"daw1665702678607__topic_d143894e1_d143895e1_d143896e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"daw1665702678607__p_d143897e1_d143898e1_d143899e1\">Syntax</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"daw1665702678607__p_d143900e1_d143901e1_d143902e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">[USER_3GL]</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"daw1665702678607__p_d143903e1_d143904e1_d143905e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DynamicLibrary</var> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">/preload</code>} {<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Function1</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code> ... <code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FunctionN</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>}</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"daw1665702678607__p_d143906e1_d143907e1_d143908e1\">For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"daw1665702678607__pre_ik2_y1n_lwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[USER_3GL]\nD:/Uniface/common/jre/bin/client/jvm.dll(JNI_CreateJavaVM)D:/Uniface/common/bin/udde.dll /preload</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"daw1665702678607__topic_d103002e1_d103003e1_d103004e1_d103005e1_d103006e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d589856e99\">Arguments</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"daw1665702678607__li_d50285e1_d50286e1_d50287e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">DynamicLibrary</var> is the library\n               name </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"daw1665702678607__li_d50288e1_d50289e1_d50290e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">/preload</code> specifies that the\n               library should be loaded at Uniface start-up </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"daw1665702678607__li_d50291e1_d50292e1_d50293e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Function</var> is the function name\n               to be made available to Uniface </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"daw1665702678607__topic_d103007e1_d103008e1_d103009e1_d103010e1_d103011e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d589856e123\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"daw1665702678607__p_d143915e1_d143916e1_d143917e1\">By default, the [USER_3GL] section lists the <span class=\"ph filepath\">jvm.dll</span>, which is required for Java call-in and XML parsing. In the default installation, this points to the JRE installed by Uniface. You can change this to point to an existing JRE installation. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[USER_3GL]\n;D:/Uniface/common/jre/bin/client/jvm.dll(JNI_CreateJavaVM)\nC:/Progra~1/Java/jre1.6.0_12/bin/client/jvm.dll(JNI_CreateJavaVM)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrd1707815497645.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Assignments</a><p>In ProcScript, the equal sign (=) assigns the result of an expression to a variable, parameter, field, or status function.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wxm1665702678676.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Specifying Libraries and Functions</a><p>The [USER_3GL] section of the assignment file describes 3GL shared libraries and/or functions that will be called by your Uniface application.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hmh1665702679533.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuring Uniface to Use a Specific JRE</a><p>You can configure Uniface to use a different Java Runtime Environment (JRE) than the one selected during installation.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yeu1719685518358.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Assignment Settings</a><p>An assignment setting is a setting or definition in an assignment file that determines one aspect of the behavior or environment of a Uniface application. Assignment settings can specify the location of application resources and servers, set environment variables, define application logicals, and set Uniface system settings to influence runtime behavior.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526720\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526720\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "[USER_3GL] Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 [USER_3GL] Use the [USER_3GL] section of the assignment file to lists third-party components and Uniface 3GL extensions to be made available to Uniface. Syntax [USER_3GL] DynamicLibrary { /preload } { ( Function1 , ... , FunctionN ) } For example: [USER_3GL] D:/Uniface/common/jre/bin/client/jvm.dll(JNI_CreateJavaVM)D:/Uniface/common/bin/udde.dll /preload Copy Arguments DynamicLibrary is the library name /preload specifies that the library should be loaded at Uniface start-up Function is the function name to be made available to Uniface Description By default, the [USER_3GL] section lists the jvm.dll , which is required for Java call-in and XML parsing. In the default installation, this points to the JRE installed by Uniface. You can change this to point to an existing JRE installation. For example: [USER_3GL] ;D:/Uniface/common/jre/bin/client/jvm.dll(JNI_CreateJavaVM) C:/Progra~1/Java/jre1.6.0_12/bin/client/jvm.dll(JNI_CreateJavaVM) Copy Related Links Assignments In ProcScript, the equal sign (=) assigns the result of an expression to a variable, parameter, field, or status function. Specifying Libraries and Functions The [USER_3GL] section of the assignment file describes 3GL shared libraries and/or functions that will be called by your Uniface application. Configuring Uniface to Use a Specific JRE You can configure Uniface to use a different Java Runtime Environment (JRE) than the one selected during installation. Assignment Settings An assignment setting is a setting or definition in an assignment file that determines one aspect of the behavior or environment of a Uniface application. Assignment settings can specify the location of application resources and servers, set environment variables, define application logicals, and set Uniface system settings to influence runtime behavior. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}